17 A. The city or ward marshal is shall be the executive officer of the court; he
18 and shall execute the orders and mandates of the court and in the. In the execution
19 thereof of these orders and mandates, and in making arrests and preserving the peace,
20 he has the same powers and authority of a sheriff. the city or ward marshal shall be
21 considered a peace officer as defined in R.S. 40:2402 with all the powers and
22 authority of regular law enforcement officers of this state except as provided in
23 Subsections C and D of this Section. The city or ward marshal and his deputy
24 marshals shall be considered officers of a public entity for the purposes of immunity
25 from liability as provided in R.S. 9:2793.1.
26 * * *
27 C.(1) Notwithstanding any provision of law to contrary, any city or ward
28 marshal who serves a population of forty thousand or less as provided in the most
29 recent federal decennial census has, along with his deputy marshals, the following
30 enumerated powers:
31 (a) Execution of attachments, bench warrants, or any other orders of arrest
32 issued by a city court within the territorial jurisdiction of the marshal.
33 (b) Detainment or the taking into custody of an individual only when
34 reasonably necessary to effectuate the service or execution of any of the following:
35 (i) Civil writs.
36 (ii) Notices of eviction.
37 (iii) Orders of seizure or attachment.
38 (iv) Any other civil process lawfully issued by a city court.
39 (c) Detainment or effecting the arrest of an individual upon order of the city
40 court for acts occurring in the city court's presence or on the grounds of the city court
41 that constitute direct contempt.
42 (d) Detainment or effecting the arrest of an individual for any violation of
43 Title 14 or 40 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950 or a local or municipal
44 ordinance in the city court's presence or on the grounds of the city court.
45 (2) In any declared state of emergency issued by both the governor and the
46 local governing authority pursuant to R.S. 29:721 et seq., the city or ward marshal
